TWA
EMPLOYEES' TIMETABLE • DOMESTIC SCHEDULES
ISSUE DATE MAY 3, 1974
EFFECTIVE JUNE 15, 1974
(Except as Noted)
This timetable is being issued to reflect the addition of new mileage and seasonal increases as allowed under capacity agree-
ments in the following markets:
NYC-LAX, NYC-SFO, ORD-SFO, WAS-LAX, NYC-DEN, PHL-SFO, WAS-LAX, WAS-DEN,
NYC-DEN.
Time and equipment changes are also being made for marketing and operational improvement. Major schedule
actions are listed below.
NEW NARROWBODY SERVICE
JFK-DEN Flights 155/156
ORD-LAS Flights 139/6711/262
IAD-DEN Flights 211/212
ORD-TUS Flights 179/106
LAS-STL E/B only Flight 432
ICT-LAX-SFO Flights 295/296
PIT-DEN Flights 173/174
ORD-DEN Flights 265/162
PHL-STL Flights 283/248
STL-DEN Flights 167/456
JFK-IND-STL Flights 373/94
DCA-ORD Flights 377/376
ORD-ICT Flights 343/330
NEW WIDE BODY SERVICE
PHL-SFO Flights 31/54 opt 1011 I.L.O. B-707
NYC-SFO Flights 41/46 opt 1011 I.L.O. B-707
WAS-LAX Flights 735/74 opt 1011 I.L.O. B-707
PIT-ORD-SFO Flights 135/130 opt 1011 I.L.O. B-707
ORD-SFO Flights 175/82 opt 1011 I.L.O. B-707
IND-STL-SFO Flights 223/446 effective July 15
TWA FORM T211-5-74 PRINTED IN U.S.A.
EMPLOYEES' TIMETABLE NO. 74-7
Cancels Employees' Timetable No. 74-6
